Given a commutative ring `k`, a group homomorphism `f : G ‚Üí* H`, a `k`-linear `H`-representation `A`, a `k`-linear `G`-representation `B`, and a representation morphism `Res(f)(A) ‚ü∂ B`, we get a cochain map `inhomogeneousCochains A ‚ü∂ inhomogeneousCochains B` and hence maps on cohomology `H‚Åø(H, A) ‚ü∂ H‚Åø(G, B)`. We also provide extra API for these maps in degrees 0, 1, 2.

In a subsequent PR we will add support for switching resolution.
